I don't feel safe with the approach in the combination of changes.

If sonic image installation needs to do fstrim, then it should not return until the fstrim is done. Otherwise, if every installation calls fstrim and prevent fast-reboot for 2 minutes, then the upgrade pipeline will never complete, because fast-reboot will always fail.
We need to discuss this change before moving forward.
I have reverted the fstrim changes and 2 minutes delay changes and updated the PR.

I would suggest to link it to the `config` and `show` utilities to have unified CLI
i.e.
```
$ show pfc priority Ethernet0

Interface    Lossless priorities
-----------  ---------------------
Ethernet0    3,4
```

And describe new CLI in the Command Reference doc
https://github.com/Azure/sonic-utilities/blob/master/doc/Command-Reference.md
